      "@type": "PropertyValue",
      "name": "description",
      "value": "Run a diagnostic k-point convergence test on a non-orthogonal cell (e.g., monoclinic ZrO₂) comparing total energy convergence vs. band-resolved quantities (band gap, band energies at high-symmetry points) across increasing k-point meshes, with and without symmetry reduction, to detect anisotropic sampling artifacts."
    },
    {
      "@type": "PropertyValue",
      "name": "expected_prediction",
      "value": "Total energy will converge to <1 meV/atom by a moderate k-mesh (e.g., 4×4×4 Gamma-centered), while the band gap and specific band energies at symmetry points will continue to fluctuate by >10 meV even at 6×6×6, especially in the non-orthogonal cell with symmetry-reduced mesh. The discrepancy will be larger for the non-orthogonal cell than for an equivalent orthogonal cell."
    },
